explanation: The solution first sorts the array to efficiently find the closest value to the target. Then, it iterates through the array, keeping track of the sum of the elements. When the sum exceeds the target, it calculates the absolute difference between the sum and the target, and the absolute difference between the target and the sum minus the current element. It returns the minimum of the current element and the element that would make the sum closest to the target.

